"```sql\nSELECT users.DisplayName\nFROM votes\nJOIN users ON votes.UserId = users.Id\nJOIN posts ON votes.PostId = posts.Id\nWHERE votes.BountyAmount = 50 AND posts.Title LIKE '%variance%'\n```\nThis SQL query selects the display name of the user who added a bounty amount of 50 to a post with a title mentioning \"variance\". It joins the `votes`, `users`, and `posts` tables using the foreign key relationships defined in the schema."